[src:perl-docs/perlre-p03] For example: `^(?>a*)ab` will never match, since `(?>a*)` (anchored at the beginning of string, as above) will match *all* characters `"a"` at the beginning of string, leaving no `"a"` for `ab` to match.
[src:perl-docs/perlre-p03] In contrast, `a*ab` will match the same as `a+b`, since the match of the subgroup `a*` is influenced by the following group `ab` (see "Backtracking").
[src:perl-docs/perlre-p03] In particular, `a*` inside `a*ab` will match fewer characters than a standalone `a*`, since this makes the tail match.
