[src:perl-docs/perlre-p04] Suppose that we want to enable a new RE escape-sequence `\Y|` which matches at a boundary between whitespace characters and non-whitespace characters.
[src:perl-docs/perlre-p04] Note that `(?=\S)(?<!\S)|(?!\S)(?<=\S)` matches exactly at these positions, so we want to have each `\Y|` in the place of the more complicated version.
[src:perl-docs/perlre-p04] Now `use customre` enables the new escape in constant regular expressions, *i.e.*, those without any runtime variable interpolations.
